overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The agent performed an
  in-depth analysis of the existing codebase, comparing it against the
  functional and content requirements. This led to the creation of a detailed
  plan outlining both fulfilled and missing features. Subsequently, the agent
  began implementing the high-priority items from the plan. This included
  integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical safety
  warnings for high scores. The agent also added robust detection and reporting
  for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and implemented logic to
  identify Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The remaining identified gaps are slated
  for future implementation.
